00:18:52.362 --> 00:18:54.570
I got it from a friend of
mine who is Middle Eastern.

00:18:54.570 --> 00:18:57.004
He donated the
recipe for the book.

00:18:57.004 --> 00:18:58.920
It's the only recipe in
there that isn't mine,

00:18:58.920 --> 00:19:00.425
and I think it's my
favorite one in the book.

00:19:00.425 --> 00:19:01.111
[LAUGHTER]

00:19:01.111 --> 00:19:02.652
SPEAKER 2: It's a
good one to choose.

00:19:02.652 --> 00:19:03.630
SPEAKER 1: Yeah.

00:19:03.630 --> 00:19:05.880
SPEAKER 2: My final question
before we'll turn it over

00:19:05.880 --> 00:19:09.060
to the audience to ask a
few questions is what advice

00:19:09.060 --> 00:19:13.860
do you have for those of us that
are meat eaters at the moment,

00:19:13.860 --> 00:19:16.290
looking to try and get more
into a plant-based diet

00:19:16.290 --> 00:19:17.484
and maybe make that switch?

00:19:17.484 --> 00:19:18.150
SPEAKER 1: Yeah.

00:19:18.150 --> 00:19:21.490
I would say just explore
foods that are out there.

00:19:21.490 --> 00:19:25.110
For me, aside from the ethical
component of changing my diet,

00:19:25.110 --> 00:19:29.370
the thing that I really got
the most out of it in terms of

00:19:29.370 --> 00:19:32.490
was just opening up my
culinary experience.

00:19:32.490 --> 00:19:33.990
Before I adopted a
plant-based diet,

00:19:33.990 --> 00:19:36.390
I was eating pretty much
the same thing every day.

00:19:36.390 --> 00:19:38.940
I was just a meat and
potatoes kind of guy.

00:19:38.940 --> 00:19:42.090
I didn't really explore that
much when it came to food.

00:19:42.090 --> 00:19:44.460
So I would just say there's
a whole wide world of foods

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:46.840
and ingredients out there
that you might find you love.

00:19:46.840 --> 00:19:51.040
If you eat a beef burger, try
an Impossible Burger or Beyond

00:19:51.040 --> 00:19:51.540
Burger.

00:19:51.540 --> 00:19:54.870
Try veggie chicken.

00:19:54.870 --> 00:19:57.480
It might not taste exactly the
same as chicken or as meat,

00:19:57.480 --> 00:19:59.940
but you might like it just
as a different food product

00:19:59.940 --> 00:20:01.230
unto itself.

00:20:01.230 --> 00:20:03.090
Not to mention all
the different things

00:20:03.090 --> 00:20:07.090
you can make kind of whole
grains and nuts and produce.

00:20:07.090 --> 00:20:09.510
SPEAKER 2: Do we have any
questions out here-- yes, sir.

00:20:09.510 --> 00:20:12.510
AUDIENCE: I'm curious,
so almost everybody has--

