chicken and products like that.

00:23:08.920 --> 00:23:10.870
I would say, from an
environmental standpoint,

00:23:10.870 --> 00:23:12.580
by all means, the
closer we can get

00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:16.960
to a whole, plant-based,
locally-sourced diet,

00:23:16.960 --> 00:23:18.760
the better off we are.

00:23:18.760 --> 00:23:21.135
Ultimately, though, even
the processed foods--

00:23:21.135 --> 00:23:22.510
if they're
plant-based or better,

00:23:22.510 --> 00:23:24.593
environmentally speaking,
because you cut out that

00:23:24.593 --> 00:23:26.010
middleman--

00:23:26.010 --> 00:23:28.690
if you take a chicken
nugget, for example--

00:23:28.690 --> 00:23:30.580
a real chicken nugget
made of chicken--

00:23:30.580 --> 00:23:33.250
you have to grow all the crops,
you have to process them still

00:23:33.250 --> 00:23:35.000
in grain mills, you
have to transport them

00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:35.850
all over the world.

00:23:35.850 --> 00:23:37.390
Then, you feed
them to a chicken.

00:23:37.390 --> 00:23:39.430
You raise the chicken,
slaughter the chicken,

00:23:39.430 --> 00:23:42.589
and then you get protein.

00:23:42.589 --> 00:23:44.380
Then, you take a
vegetarian chicken nugget,

00:23:44.380 --> 00:23:45.855
for example, same process.

00:23:45.855 --> 00:23:47.230
You still have to
grow the crops.

00:23:47.230 --> 00:23:48.379
You have to process them.

00:23:48.379 --> 00:23:50.420
You just turn it directly
into the chicken nugget

00:23:50.420 --> 00:23:53.530
rather than going through
that middleman first.

00:23:53.530 --> 00:23:55.320
Still has an
environmental footprint.

00:23:55.320 --> 00:23:58.519
It's not, by any means,
a zero-footprint food.

00:23:58.519 --> 00:24:00.310
But it's much more
efficient because you've

00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:01.765
cut out that middleman.

00:24:01.765 --> 00:24:03.140
But, yeah, at the
end of the day,

00:24:03.140 --> 00:24:05.681
the closer we can get to whole
plant-based foods, the better.

