00:26:31.720 --> 00:26:33.553
So the question was the
environmental impact

00:26:33.553 --> 00:26:35.520
of chicken compared to beef.

00:26:35.520 --> 00:26:37.790
Beef has its own
special set of problems.

00:26:37.790 --> 00:26:42.190
Cows are very gaseous animals,
especially when they eat grass,

00:26:42.190 --> 00:26:44.800
because of the way
their digestion works.

00:26:44.800 --> 00:26:47.380
They emit a lot of methane,
which is a major problem.

00:26:47.380 --> 00:26:49.870
Chickens emit less
methane on the whole.

00:26:49.870 --> 00:26:51.250
But there's so
much more of them.

00:26:51.250 --> 00:26:52.976
There's so much more chickens.

00:26:52.976 --> 00:26:54.850
Because they're smaller,
we need more of them

00:26:54.850 --> 00:26:56.090
to sustain the food supply.

00:26:56.090 --> 00:26:59.350
So in the US, we have about
10 billion farm animals.

00:26:59.350 --> 00:27:03.390
About 9.5 billion of those
animals are chickens.

00:27:03.390 --> 00:27:04.660
Nearly all of them--

00:27:04.660 --> 00:27:07.180
more than 9 out of every
10 animals in the US

00:27:07.180 --> 00:27:09.799
is a chicken when it
comes to our food supply.

00:27:09.799 --> 00:27:11.590
And so some of the
biggest problems related

00:27:11.590 --> 00:27:13.600
to chicken farming are where
do we put all these animals?

00:27:13.600 --> 00:27:15.400
That's why we put them into
suburban neighborhoods,

00:27:15.400 --> 00:27:16.571
like the one I talked about.

00:27:16.571 --> 00:27:17.570
Where does the waste go?

00:27:17.570 --> 00:27:18.528
It ends up in the land.

00:27:18.528 --> 00:27:21.304
It ends up in the waterways.

00:27:21.304 --> 00:27:22.720
We have so many
chickens, we don't

00:27:22.720 --> 00:27:24.428
know what to do with
them or their waste,

00:27:24.428 --> 00:27:27.520
and it's a major
environmental catastrophe.

00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:28.810
Cows-- also not a great.

00:27:28.810 --> 00:27:31.150
A lot of methane
contribution from them

00:27:31.150 --> 00:27:34.120
in terms of their
digestion process.

00:27:34.120 --> 00:27:35.620
Seafood is another issue.

00:27:35.620 --> 00:27:37.480
We're pulling so many
fish out of the ocean

00:27:37.480 --> 00:27:38.855
now that scientists
say we're not

00:27:38.855 --> 00:27:42.940
going to have any left by 2048,
which is not that far from now.

00:27:42.940 --> 00:27:45.680
Fish farming, as well-- huge
environmental footprint.

00:27:45.680 --> 00:27:52.807
I would say, on the whole,
moving more away from seafood,

00:27:52.807 --> 00:27:54.640
more away from poultry,
more away from beef,

00:27:54.640 --> 00:27:56.990
is probably the best bet.

